===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|ls=ic|大|口|子|t1=adult|t2=mouth|t3=child}} – to transmit knowledge. In western Zhou {{w|bronze inscriptions}}, {{och-l|*甘}} started being added. As time went by, {{och-l|*子}} corrupted into {{och-l|*于}}, {{zh-l|*大}} into {{och-l|*矢}}, and {{och-l|*甘}} into {{och-l|*白}}, giving rise to the form seen in the {{w|Shuowen Jiezi}} ({{och-l|*𥏼}}). The component {{och-l|*于}} was dropped around the {{w|Han_dynasty#Western_Han|Western Han}}, arriving at the modern form.

===Etymology===
Exopassive of {{och-l|知|to know}}, literally “what is known > knowledge”.

